<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-02-15T10:29:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-02-15T10:29:00-05:00" n="11" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d11">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">837.00/1516: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gonzales</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-02-15T10:00:00-05:29"><hi rend="italic">February
                                            15, 1919, 10 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received 1.13 p.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>69. My February 12th, 11 a.m. and February 13th, 2 p.m. Statement
                                given to press today. The President anxious to have General Crowder
                                come at once as present Congress is agitating election reform
                                law.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzales</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>